⎩394⎭
⎩395⎭
  (literal) {⎩396⎭
      ⌈⎩397⎭
   Inside definitions only, pushes compiled literal to stack ⎩398⎭
⎩399⎭
       Certain Forth words are only applicable inside compiled sequences of subroutines ⎩400⎭
       Literals are handled in different ways when interpreted when in the REPL vs⎩401⎭
       compiled into sequences of subrs ⎩402⎭
       In the REPL, when we encounter a literal, we simply push it onto the stack ⎩403⎭
       In the compiler, though, we have to create an instruction that pushes ⎩404⎭
	 the literal onto the stack. ⎩405⎭
	 Compiled code doesn't do what the REPL does, we have to hard-wire and ⎩406⎭
	 bake in code that pushes the literal when the time comes to run the sequence. ⎩407⎭
⎩408⎭
       This word - "(literal)" - is a simple case and one could actually type this ⎩409⎭
	 instruction into the REPL, but, that would be redundant.  Other kinds of words, ⎩410⎭
	 e.g. some control-flow words, tend to be messier and the code below only handles ⎩411⎭
	 the compiled aspects and ignores the REPL aspects ⎩412⎭
⎩413⎭
       "IP" is the current word index in a sequence of words being compiled. ⎩414⎭
  ⌉⎩415⎭
      defsynonym lit ≡ State.RAM [State.IP]⎩416⎭
      %push (lit)⎩417⎭
      State.IP ⇐ State.IP + 1 ⌈ move past this item (the literal) - we're done with it ⌉⎩418⎭
  }⎩419⎭
⎩420⎭
  branch {⎩421⎭
      ⌈ This instruction appears only inside subroutine sequences, jump to address in next cell ⌉⎩422⎭
      ⌈ This instruction is inserted into a subr sequence when compiling control-flow words, like "else" see below) ⌉⎩423⎭
      State.IP ⇐ State.RAM [State.IP]⎩424⎭
      ⌈ normally, we just execute an instruction then move the IP sequentially forward by 1 unit, i.e. IP ⇐ IP + 1 ⌉⎩425⎭
      ⌈   in this case, though, we explicitly change the IP to some other value and don't just increment it ⌉⎩426⎭
  }⎩427⎭
⎩428⎭
  0branch {⎩429⎭
      ⌈ This instruction appears only inside subroutine sequences, jump on false to address in next cell ⌉⎩430⎭
      deftemp test ⇐ %toboolean (%pop)⎩431⎭
      if (test) {⎩432⎭
	  State.IP ⇐ State.IP + 1⎩433⎭
      } else {⎩434⎭
	 State.IP ⇐ State.RAM [State.IP]⎩435⎭
      }⎩436⎭
  }⎩437⎭
⎩438⎭
⎩439⎭
  ⌈ "immediate" words are fully operational even when in compile mode. Some (not all) of these words are meant to⎩440⎭
      work /only/ in compile mode. At the REPL prompt ("interpret" mode), they produce unwanted results.⎩441⎭
    immediate words: xif, xelse, xthen, xquote, xcomment, xsemi⎩442⎭
    immediate words that only have meaning in compile mode: xif, xelse, xthen, xsemi⎩443⎭
  ⌉⎩444⎭
⎩445⎭
⎩446⎭
  ⌈ IF, ELSE and THEN are "immediate" words - they should only be used inside of ":" (colon compiler) ⌉⎩447⎭
⎩448⎭
  ⌈ see diagram compiling-IF-THEN.drawio.png ⌉⎩449⎭
  %immediate ❲if❳ { ⎩450⎭
      ⌈ This instruction appears only inside subroutine sequences, ( f -- ) compile if test and branchFalse ⌉ ⎩451⎭
      ⌈ Step. 1: generate conditional branch to yet-unknown target1 ⌉ ⎩452⎭
      deftemp branchFalseAddress ⇐ %funcall _find ("0branch")⎩453⎭
      %ram+ (branchFalseAddress) ⌈ insert branch-if-false opcode (word) ⌉ ⎩454⎭
      %rpush (%RAMnext) ⌈ target1 onto r-stack as memo for later fixup ⌉ ⎩455⎭
      defsynonym target1 ≡ -1 ⎩456⎭
      %ram+ (target1) ⌈ branch target will be fixed up later ⌉ ⎩457⎭
      ⌈ Step. 2: generate code for true branch - return to compiler which will compile the following words ⌉ ⎩458⎭
      ⌈ THEN or ELSE will do the fixup of target1 ⌉ ⎩459⎭
  }⎩460⎭
⎩461⎭
  ⌈ see diagram compiling-IF-ELSE-THEN.drawio.png ⌉⎩462⎭
  %immediate ❲else❳ {⎩463⎭
      ⌈ Step. 1: fixup target1 from IF-true, retrieving memo from R-stack ⌉⎩464⎭
      deftemp target1 ⇐ %rpop⎩465⎭
      State.RAM [target1] ⇐ %RAMnext⎩466⎭
      ⌈ Step. 2: generate unconditional branch for preceding IF, creating new memo for target2 on R-stack ⌉⎩467⎭
      deftemp brAddress ⇐ %funcall _find ("branch")⎩468⎭
      %rpush (%RAMnext) ⌈ target2 address on R-stack as memo for later fixup ⌉⎩469⎭
      defsynonym target2 ≡ -1⎩470⎭
      %ram+ (target2) ⌈ branch target will be fixed up later ⌉⎩471⎭
      ⌈ Step. 3: generate code for false branch - return to compiler which will compile the following words ⌉⎩472⎭
      ⌈ THEN will do the fixup of target2 ⌉⎩473⎭
  }⎩474⎭
⎩475⎭
  ⌈ see diagrams compiling-IF-THEN.drawio.png and compiling-IF-ELSE-THEN.drawio.png ⌉⎩476⎭
  %immediate ❲then❳ {⎩477⎭
      ⌈ Step. 1: fixup target (from IF or from ELSE, above), retrieving memo from R-stack ⌉⎩478⎭
      deftemp target ⇐ %rpop⎩479⎭
      State.RAM [target] ⇐ %RAMnext⎩480⎭
  }⎩481⎭
⎩482⎭
  (do) {⎩483⎭
      ⌈ ( limit index --) Puts limit and index on return stack. ⌉⎩484⎭
      @xswap⎩485⎭
      deftemp index ⇐ %pop⎩486⎭
      deftemp limit ⇐ %pop⎩487⎭
      %rpush (index)⎩488⎭
      %rpush (limit)⎩489⎭
  }⎩490⎭
⎩491⎭
  %immediate ❲do❳ {⎩492⎭
      ⌈ (  limit index --) Begin counted loop. ⌉⎩493⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("(do)"))  ⌈ Push do loop handler. ⌉⎩494⎭
      %rpush(%RAMnext)           ⌈ Push address to jump back to. ⌉⎩495⎭
  }⎩496⎭
⎩497⎭
  (loop) {⎩498⎭
      ⌈ (  -- f) Determine if loop is done. ⌉⎩499⎭
      deftemp index ⇐ %rpop⎩500⎭
      deftemp limit ⇐ %rpop⎩501⎭
      defsynonym cond ≡ (index >= limit)⎩502⎭
      %push (cond)⎩503⎭
      if (cond) { ⌈ clean up rstack if index >= limit ⌉⎩504⎭
	  %rpop⎩505⎭
	  %rpop⎩506⎭
      }  ⎩507⎭
  }⎩508⎭
⎩509⎭
  %immediate +loop {⎩510⎭
      ⌈ ( --) Close counted loop. ⌉⎩511⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("(loop)"))   ⌈ Compile in loop test. ⌉⎩512⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("0branch"))  ⌈ Compile in branch check. ⌉⎩513⎭
      %ram+(%rpop)           ⌈ Address to jump back to. ⌉⎩514⎭
  }⎩515⎭
⎩516⎭
  %immediate ❲loop❳ {⎩517⎭
      ⌈ (  --) Close counted loop. ⌉⎩518⎭
      %push (1)⎩519⎭
      @literalize                  ⌈ Default loop increment for x_loop. ⌉⎩520⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("(loop)"))   ⌈ Compile in loop test. ⌉⎩521⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("0branch"))  ⌈ Compile in branch check. ⌉⎩522⎭
      %ram+(%rpop)           ⌈ Address to jump back to. ⌉⎩523⎭
  }⎩524⎭
⎩525⎭
  %immediate ❲begin❳ {⎩526⎭
      %rpush (%RAMnext)  ⌈ ( --) Start indefinite loop. ⌉⎩527⎭
  }⎩528⎭
⎩529⎭
  %immediate ❲until❳ {⎩530⎭
      ⌈ (  f --) Close indefinite loop with test. ⌉⎩531⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("0branch"))  ⌈ Expects result of test on stack. ⌉⎩532⎭
      %ram+(%rpop)           ⌈ Address to jump back to. ⌉⎩533⎭
  }⎩534⎭
⎩535⎭
⎩536⎭
⎩537⎭
  ⌈  "... 123 constant K ..." ⌉⎩538⎭
  ⌈  at interpretation time: 123 is on the Stack, we have consumed "constant" from BUFF, BUFF now contains "K ..." ⌉⎩539⎭
  ⌈  invoke 'word' which parses "K" and pushed it. The stack becomes [... 123 "K"] ⌉⎩540⎭
  ⌈  pop "K", pop 123, create a new word called 'K' with its PFA set to 123 and its CFA set to a subr that⎩541⎭
       gets 123 from its PFA and pushes it onto the stack ⌉⎩542⎭
  ❲const❳ {⎩543⎭
      ⌈  get next word - the name - from BUFF ⌉⎩544⎭
      defsynonym blank ≡ 32⎩545⎭
      %push (blank)⎩546⎭
      @xword⎩547⎭
      ⌈  stack is now: ( NNNN name -- ) ⌉⎩548⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩549⎭
      deftemp value ⇐ %pop⎩550⎭
      defsynonym normal ≡ 0⎩551⎭
      deftemp fobj ⇐ %funcall code (name, normal, ↪︎doconst)⎩552⎭
      %ram+ (value)⎩553⎭
  }⎩554⎭
⎩555⎭
  , {⎩556⎭
      %funcall comma (%pop)⎩557⎭
  }⎩558⎭
⎩559⎭
  variable {⎩560⎭
      defsynonym blank ≡ 32⎩561⎭
      %push (blank)⎩562⎭
      @xword⎩563⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩564⎭
      deftemp value ⇐ %pop⎩565⎭
      %funcall fvar (name, value)    ⎩566⎭
  }⎩567⎭
⎩568⎭
  dump {⎩569⎭
      deftemp n ⇐ %toint (%pop)⎩570⎭
      deftemp start ⇐ %toint (%pop)⎩571⎭
      %print ("----------------------------------------------------------------")⎩572⎭
      deftemp a ⇐ start⎩573⎭
      while (a < start + (%funcall min (n, (%funcall len (State.RAM) - start)))) {⎩574⎭
	  %print (a)⎩575⎭
	  %print (": ")⎩576⎭
	  %print (State.RAM [a])⎩577⎭
	  %eol⎩578⎭
	  deftemp a ⇐ a + 1⎩579⎭
      }⎩580⎭
  }⎩581⎭
⎩582⎭
  ! {⎩583⎭
      deftemp b ⇐ %pop⎩584⎭
      deftemp a ⇐ %pop⎩585⎭
      State.RAM [b] ⇐ a⎩586⎭
  }⎩587⎭
⎩588⎭
  bye { ⌈ ( --) Leave interpreter ⌉ %quit }⎩589⎭
⎩590⎭
⎩591⎭
  find {⎩592⎭
      ⌈ "( name | -- (name 0)|(xt 1)|(xt -1)) Search for word name." ⌉⎩593⎭
      ⌈ 3 possible results: 1. (name 0) if not found, 2. (xt 1) if found and word is immediate, 3. (xt -1) if found and word is normal ⌉⎩594⎭
      %push (32)⎩595⎭
      @xword⎩596⎭
      deftemp found ⇐ %funcall _find(%stop)⎩597⎭
      if (0 = found) {⎩598⎭
	  %push (0)⎩599⎭
      } else {⎩600⎭
	  %pop  ⌈ # Get rid of name on stack. ⌉⎩601⎭
	  %push(found)⎩602⎭
	  deftemp immediate ⇐ -1⎩603⎭
	  if (State.RAM[%stop - 1] & 1) { immediate ⇐ 1 }⎩604⎭
	  %push(immediate)⎩605⎭
      }⎩606⎭
  }⎩607⎭
⎩608⎭
  ' {⎩609⎭
      ⌈ "( name -- xt|-1) Search for execution token of word name." ⌉⎩610⎭
      %push (32)⎩611⎭
      @xword⎩612⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩613⎭
      deftemp found ⇐ %funcall _find(name)⎩614⎭
      %push (found)⎩615⎭
  }⎩616⎭
⎩617⎭
  None {⎩618⎭
      %pushNone⎩619⎭
  }⎩620⎭
⎩621⎭
  words {⎩622⎭
      ⌈ print words in dictionary ⌉⎩623⎭
      deftemp x ⇐ State.LAST⎩624⎭
      while (x > -1) {⎩625⎭
	  %print (State.RAM [x+ 1])⎩626⎭
	  %print (" ")⎩627⎭
      }⎩628⎭
      %eol⎩629⎭
  }⎩630⎭
⎩631⎭
⎩632⎭
  execute {⎩633⎭
      ⌈ invoke given word ⌉⎩634⎭
      deftemp wordAddress ⇐ %pop⎩635⎭
      @@wordAddress⎩636⎭
  }⎩637⎭
⎩638⎭
⎩639⎭
  : {⎩640⎭
      ⌈ ( name | --) Start compilation. ⌉⎩641⎭
      defsynonym blank ≡ 32⎩642⎭
      %push (blank)⎩643⎭
      @xword⎩644⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩645⎭
      %funcall code(name, 0, doword)⎩646⎭
      %setCompilingState⎩647⎭
  }⎩648⎭
⎩649⎭
  %immediate ; {⎩650⎭
      ⌈ ( --) Finish definition. ⌉⎩651⎭
⎩652⎭
      %ram+(-1)  ⌈ Marker for end of definition. ⌉⎩653⎭
      %setNotCompilingState⎩654⎭
  }⎩655⎭
⎩656⎭
  interpret {⎩657⎭
      ⌈ ( string --) Execute word. ⌉⎩658⎭
⎩659⎭
      @find⎩660⎭
      ⌈ 3 possible results from find:⎩661⎭
	  1. (name 0) if not found,⎩662⎭
	  2. (xt 1) if found and word is immediate,⎩663⎭
	  3. (xt -1) if found and word is normal ⌉⎩664⎭
      deftemp result ⇐ %pop					    defsynonym foundimmediate ≡ (result = 1)⎩665⎭
      deftemp item ⇐ %pop						    defsynonym foundnormal ≡ (result = -1)⎩666⎭
								      defsynonym notfound ≡ (result = 0)⎩667⎭
								      defsynonym found ≡ (foundimmediate or foundnormal)⎩668⎭
⎩669⎭
if (found) {⎩670⎭
    if (%incompilingstate) {⎩671⎭
        if (foundimmediate) {⎩672⎭
            λexec(item)⎩673⎭
        } else {⎩674⎭
            λcompileword(item)⎩675⎭
        }⎩676⎭
        ⎩677⎭
    } else {⎩678⎭
        λexec(item)⎩679⎭
    }⎩680⎭
    ⎩681⎭
} else {⎩682⎭
    if (%incompilingstate) {⎩683⎭
        if (%isinteger(item)) {⎩684⎭
            λcompileinteger(item)⎩685⎭
        } else {⎩686⎭
            if (%isfloat(item)) {⎩687⎭
                λcompilefloat(item)⎩688⎭
            } else {⎩689⎭
                @returnFalse⎩690⎭
            }⎩691⎭
            ⎩692⎭
        }⎩693⎭
        ⎩694⎭
    } else {⎩695⎭
        if (%isinteger(item)) {⎩696⎭
            λpushasinteger(item)⎩697⎭
        } else {⎩698⎭
            if (%isfloat(item)) {⎩699⎭
                λpushasfloat(item)⎩700⎭
            } else {⎩701⎭
                @returnFalse⎩702⎭
            }⎩703⎭
            ⎩704⎭
        }⎩705⎭
        ⎩706⎭
    }⎩707⎭
    ⎩708⎭
}⎩709⎭
⎩710⎭
      return True⎩711⎭
}⎩712⎭
}⎩713⎭
⎩714⎭
invoke {⎩715⎭
  @ok⎩716⎭
}⎩717⎭